Package org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.log.reverse

Class EagerlyReversedTransactionCursor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.impl.transaction.log.reverse.EagerlyReversedTransactionCursor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Supplier<CommittedTransactionRepresentation>, IOCursor<CommittedTransactionRepresentation>, RawCursor<CommittedTransactionRepresentation,​IOException>, TransactionCursor
    public class EagerlyReversedTransactionCursor
extends Object
implements TransactionCursor
    Eagerly exhausts a TransactionCursor and allows moving through it in reverse order. The idea is that this should only be done for a subset of a bigger transaction log stream, typically for one log file. For reversing a transaction log consisting of multiple log files ReversedMultiFileTransactionCursor should be used (it will use this class internally though).
    See Also:
    ReversedMultiFileTransactionCursor
